--help

***Parsing arguments:***

Request to upload: --help

***Required arguments not found.***

Usage:
  java -jar DVUploader-1.2.0.jar -server=<serverURL> -key=<apikey> -did=<dataset DOI> <files or directories>

  where:
      <serverUrl> = the URL of the server to upload to, e.g. https://datverse.tdl.org
      <apiKey> = your personal apikey, created in the dataverse server at <serverUrl>
      <did> = the Dataset DOI you are uploading to, e.g. doi:10.5072/A1B2C3
      <files or directories> = a space separated list of files to upload or directory name(s) where the files to upload are

  Optional Arguments:
      -uploadviaserver    - Use Dataverse's indirect upload capability. This makes temporary copies of files on the Dataverse server, puts a greater workload on the server and is not suitable for large files, but it can be used when direct uploads are not enabled for a given dataset.
      -listonly           - Scan the Dataset and local files and list what would be uploaded (does not upload with this flag)
      -limit=<n>          - Specify a maximum number of files to upload per invocation.
      -verify             - Check both the file name and checksum in comparing with current Dataset entries.
      -skip=<n>           - a number of files to skip before starting processing (saves time when you know the first n files have been uploaded before)
      -recurse            - recurse into subdirectories
      -maxlockwait        - the maximum time to wait (in seconds) for a Dataset lock (i.e. while the last file is ingested) to expire (default 60 seconds)
      -trustall           - trust all server certificates (i.e. for use when testing with self-signed server certificates)
      -singlefile         - send each file to the server separately (only affects directupload/ when -uploadviaserver is not set)
      -noIngest           - Tells Dataverse to not ingest tabular files upon upload
      -failOnInvalidNames - Tells Dataverse to not ingest tabular files upon upload
      -bag=<URL>          - 'alpha' capbility to create a dataset from a Bag exported by Dataverse. <URL> is the location of the Bag to process.
      -createIn=<alias>   - required for Bag import: the alias of the Dataverse you want to create a dataset in

See https://github.com/GlobalDataverseCommunityConsortium/dataverse-uploader/wiki/DVUploader,-a-Command-line-Bulk-Uploader-for-Dataverse for more usage information.


